race.description: Semco Equipment Sales Country Boosted Handicap
race.comment: DANCING MAN (12) was quickly back on track, scoring easily in Maidens at this venue/distance. Draws to advantage and keeps the handy 3kg claim. Doubt this is much harder and he can take the next step. The veteran VAINSTREAM (5) was outgraded two back at Rosehill, but the form around that stacks right up. There was only a nose in it at Wagga at this level last time, and he gets in well with the 2kg claim. He's capable of using the inside barrier and should go close. PRINCE PAPA (7) arrives off an easy 50 win at Canberra when staking the lead. He's come back improved, but has an awkward gate to contend with here. NOCTUA (4) won a 60 at Canberra and then tackled a CL2 there and wasn't too far away. This suits her better, and she also has claims.
